<h1>\{{eui-checkbox}}</h1>


<h4 id="section-class">class <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Assigns a custom CSS class to the checkbox.
</p>


<h4 id="section-size">size <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  Controls the size of the checkbox.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>medium (default)</li>
</ul>
<p>
  Additional sizes can be added via CSS. See {{link-to "Theming" "documentation.theming"}}
</p>


<h4 id="section-style">style <span>string</span></h4>
<p>
  The aesthetic style of the button.
</p>

<h5>Values</h5>
<ul class="defaults">
  <li>default (default)</li>
</ul>

<pre>\{{#eui-checkbox style="default"}}Remember me\{{/eui-checkbox}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{#eui-checkbox style="default"}}Remember me{{/eui-checkbox}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-disabled">disabled <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  Disables the checkbox.
</p>

<pre>\{{#eui-checkbox disabled=true}}Unchecked\{{/eui-checkbox}}
\{{#eui-checkbox value=true disabled=true}}Checked\{{/eui-checkbox}}</pre>

<div class="output">
  {{#eui-checkbox disabled=true}}
    Unchecked
  {{/eui-checkbox}}

  {{#eui-checkbox value=true disabled=true}}
    Checked
  {{/eui-checkbox}}
</div>


<h4 id="section-error">error <span>boolean | string</span></h4>
<p>
  Responsible for validation and error handling. See {{link-to "Error Handling" "documentation.errorhandling"}}
</p>


<h4 id="section-forceerrorcheck">forceErrorCheck <span>boolean</span></h4>
<p>
  If set to <em>true</em> the input will force an error check, even if the value is blank.
</p>


<h4 id="section-onchange">onChange <span>string | action</span></h4>
<p>
  If you specify an <em>onChange</em> action the original state will not be changed and instead your action will be fired with the new value.
</p>
